The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Guus Hiddink confirmed as Russia coach

 Hiddink

Moscow: Dutchman Guus Hiddink will take over as coach of Russias national soccer team after this years World Cup, the Football Union of Russia said on Wednesday. 

The Russia Union said Hiddink had agreed a two and a half year contract and would travel to Moscow to sign it on Friday. 

For the first two years Hiddink will receive two million euros ($2.43 million), and if all goes well the contract could be extended to 2010. 

Hiddink has said previously that his backroom team would be a combination of Dutch and Russian staff. 

I will form a Dutch staff but also with a Russian who knows Russian football, said Hiddink. We have to analyse the situation and get the team afloat. 

